description: From Middle English miswriten, from Old English miswrītan, misƿrītan (“to write incorrectly; make a mistake in writing; miswrite”), equivalent to mis- +‎ write.

examples: Line fluctuations can cause misreads and miswrites.

verbs.description: miswrite (third-person singular simple present miswrites, present participle miswriting, simple past miswrote, past participle miswritten)

examples: […]  but we lose ever and anon a word, or a verse, and substitute something of our own, and thus miswrite the poem.
